  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Prevention, Diagnosis and Management of Non-Communicable Diseases in Namibia and Botswana</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Healthcare Workers; CHWs; M&amp;E officers</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Namibia, the project aims to contribute to the capacity of the Namibian government to manage non-communicable diseases (NCDs) and the reduction of maternal, neonatal and NCD-related morbidity and mortality rates through improved prevention, diagnosis and management of diabetes, hypertension and asthma and provision of maternal care in Namibia. In Botswana, the project aims to facilitate the strengthening of the Botswanan government efforts to achieve Universal Health Coverage and the implementation of the National Primary Care Guidelines through contributing to the reduction of NCD morbidity and mortality through improved prevention, diagnosis and management of diabetes, hypertension and asthma at primary health care level.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Namibia: 1) Improved capacity of health care workers and Community Health Workers (CHWs) to deliver quality maternal, newborn and child health (MNCH) and NCDS management; 2) Capacity building of the Ministry of Health in system strengthening in the management of NCDs; 3) Improved health and well-being of community members. Botswana: 1) Improved quality of health care services for the management of NCDs at primary health care level; 2) Increased public awareness on healthy lifestyles and the impact of NCDs; 3) Increased government coordination, planning and investment for NCDs.</narrative>
  </description>
